don't%20recognize%20their%20emotional%20needs%20and%2C%20deep%20down%2C%20don't%20think%20they%20are%20important%2C%20Israa%20Nasir%2C%20a%20therapist%20based%20in%20New%20York%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20pleasers%20don't%20simply%20want%20to%20make%20others%20happy%2C%20but%20fear%20them%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efeeling%20uncomfortable%20or%20upset%2C%20Summer%20Forlenza%2C%20a%20trauma%20therapist%20based%20in%20California%2C%20told%20BI.%20It%20feels%20threatening%20and%20jolts%20them%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Ffight-flight-freeze-fawn%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20%26quot%3Bfawn%20response%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20when%20someone%20reacts%20to%20a%20threat%20by%20suppressing%20their%20feelings%20to%20appease%20someone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20typically%20a%20behavior%20we%20learn%20in%20childhood%20if%20we%20feel%20the%20need%20to%20take%20care%20of%20a%20parent%20or%20other%20significant%20person%20in%20order%20for%20our%20needs%20to%20be%20met%2C%20Melissa%20Stanger%2C%20a%20psychotherapist%20based%20in%20New%20York%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20need%20to%20minimize%20your%20own%20needs%20in%20favor%20of%20theirs%2C%20either%20to%20make%20them%20the%20available%20caretaker%20that%20you%20need%20or%20because%20they%20don't%20have%20room%20for%20your%20needs%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20people%20pleaser%20is%20often%20not%20consciously%20aware%20that%20they're%20doing%20it%2C%20and%20this%20common%20but%20misunderstood%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-your-parents-behaviors-shape-who-you-are-today-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epattern%20of%20behavior%3C%2Fa%3E%20often%20leads%20to%20challenges%20in%20adult%20life.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENasir%2C%20Forlenza%2C%20and%20Stanger%20told%20BI%20the%20common%20issues%20their%20people-pleasing%20clients%20bring%20to%20therapy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227f731329-05ac-49d2-9c0a-7441e1c9b5a4%5C%22%3E1)%20Relationship%20problems%20%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20pleasers%20often%20seek%20therapy%20because%20of%20conflict%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbreadwinning-wives-make-more-than-husbands-share-what-its-like%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresentment%20in%20their%20relationships%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Stanger%20said.%20But%20they%20won't%20necessarily%20realize%20that%20these%20issues%20are%20a%20result%20of%20their%20people-pleasing%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20will%20say%2C%20'I'm%20having%20this%20conflict%20with%20a%20partner%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20know%20how%20to%20address%20it.'%20And%20usually%2C%20they%20do%20know%20how%20to%20address%20it.%20They%20just%20don't%20want%20to%20address%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20That's%20because%20they're%20afraid%20of%20jeopardizing%20the%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20people%20pleaser%20self-abandons%20again%20and%20again%20by%20prioritizing%20the%20relational%20threat%20over%20themself%2C%26quot%3B%20Nasir%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20being%20honest%20about%20their%20feelings%20can%20create%20resentment%20over%20time%2C%20which%20will%20likely%20be%20communicated%20in%20other%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20times%2C%20people%20pleasers%20will%20tolerate%20a%20lot%20of%20pain%20before%20saying%20something%2C%20and%20usually%20they'll%20say%20it%20in%20a%20very%20passive-aggressive%20or%20a%20breakdown%20type%20of%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Nasir%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20instead%20of%20communicating%20what%20she%20could%20realistically%20afford%2C%20one%20of%20Nasir's%20clients%20spent%20above%20her%20means%20and%20became%20resentful%20toward%20a%20friend%20who%20made%20more%20money%20than%20her%20and%20suggested%20expensive%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20had%20made%20the%20assumption%20that%20her%20friend%20wouldn't%20understand%20and%20started%20to%20dislike%20her%20friend%20based%20on%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Nasir%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20happens%20often%20with%20people%20pleasers%20who%20don't%20communicate%20their%20needs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22720b743c-cac3-4d73-80fa-e76668869b43%5C%22%3E2)%20Difficulty%20making%20decisions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENasir%20says%20her%20people%20pleaser%20clients%20often%20experience%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-big-decisions-work-habits-life-coach-advice-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Banalysis%20paralysis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20finding%20it%20hard%20to%20make%20decisions%2C%20particularly%20in%20relation%20to%20their%20job%2C%20living%20situation%2C%20relationship%2C%20or%20other%20personal%20circumstances.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20client%20stayed%20in%20an%20unfulfilling%20job%20for%20a%20long%20time%20rather%20than%20applying%20for%20a%20promotion%20or%20another%20role%20at%20the%20company%20because%20she%20was%20so%20worried%20about%20making%20the%20wrong%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForlenza%20said%20the%20stress%20of%20wanting%20to%20%26quot%3Bkeep%20everybody%20happy%26quot%3B%20adds%20to%20this%20indecision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20a%20lot%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fwhat-is-anxiety%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanxiety%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20fear%20at%20the%20possibility%20of%20people%20being%20upset%20with%20me%20for%20making%20this%20choice%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20of%20people%20pleasers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22989e6591-e317-4ff7-b59f-fbe906356323%5C%22%3E3)%20Emotional%20and%20workplace%20burnout%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20can%20happen%20if%20a%20people%20pleaser%20is%20scared%20to%20tell%20their%20manager%20they've%20been%20given%20too%20much%20work%2C%20for%20example.%20Forlenza%20said%20her%20clients%20can%20also%20have%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnearly-half-american-workers-dont-take-all-their-pto-research-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehard%20time%20taking%20their%20PTO%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20they%20worry%20it'll%20make%20their%20co-workers'%20lives%20harder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20a%20total%20recipe%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fburnout-work-boss-left-office-on-stretcher-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eburnout%20and%20exhaustion%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENasir%20had%20a%20client%20who%20struggled%20to%20take%20time%20off%20from%20his%20job%20in%20healthcare%20and%20fainted%20from%20exhaustion%20during%20a%20double%20shift.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmotional%20exhaustion%20or%20%26quot%3Brelational%20burnout%26quot%3B%20is%20also%20common%20among%20people%20pleasers%2C%20as%20they%20may%20feel%20they%20are%20always%20taking%20care%20of%20others%20but%20nobody%20takes%20care%20of%20them%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20pleasers%20will%20often%20know%20how%20to%20check%20the%20emotional%20temperature%20of%20a%20room%20and%20anticipate%20other%20people's%20needs%20very%20quickly%2C%20Nasir%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bso%20it's%20a%20lot%20of%20cognitive%20workload.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225914%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20paying%20in%20a%20restaurant%20using%20a%20card.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ae2859eb4be2fff9a48fed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223896%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOne%20client%20resented%20her%20friends%20for%20planning%20expensive%20activities.%20%3Cp%3E10'000%20Hours%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222a6411ac-f257-4039-b879-94f3b520b7d2%5C%22%3EPractice%20speaking%20your%20mind%20to%20reduce%20the%20urge%20to%20people-please.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%2