Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-using-w2-employees-not-gig-workers-make-some-deliveries-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDoorDash%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20anti-competitive%20business%20practices%20that%20Uber%20says%20inflate%20costs%20for%20both%20restaurants%20and%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20complaint%2C%20Uber%20alleges%20that%20DoorDash%2C%20the%20largest%20provider%20of%20restaurant%20delivery%20services%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20has%20%26quot%3Bdevised%20and%20is%20engaged%20in%20an%20unlawful%20scheme%20to%20stifle%20competition%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdrive-for-uber-eats-after-layoff-would-not-recommend-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUber%20Eats%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20making%20it%20difficult%20and%20expensive%20for%20restaurants%20to%20partner%20with%20more%20than%20one%20delivery%20service%20and%20allowing%20the%20delivery%20giant%20to%20charge%20customers%20higher%20fees%20for%20%26quot%3Blower-quality%20service.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRestaurants%20simply%20cannot%20afford%20to%20stand%20up%20to%20DoorDash%2C%20and%20find%20themselves%20powerless%20to%20choose%20the%20service%20or%20services%20that%20are%20best%20for%20their%20businesses%20in%20the%20market%20for%20first-party%20delivery%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20complaint%2C%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider%2C%20reads.%20%26quot%3BUber's%20restaurant-customers%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehave%20reported%20feeling%20like%20they%20have%20a%20'gun%20to%20their%20head%2C'%20that%20DoorDash%20is%20a%20'monopolist%2C'%20and%20that%20they%20are%20being%20bullied%20by%20DoorDash.%20But%20most%20restaurants%20have%20no%20meaningful%20option%20to%20resist%20DoorDash%2C%20given%20the%20power%20it%20wields%20through%20the%20DoorDash%20App%20in%20Third-Party%20Delivery.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20says%20DoorDash's%20alleged%20anti-competitive%20behavior%20has%20cost%20Uber%20millions%20in%20terminated%20and%20potential%20revenue%20streams.%20The%20suit%20seeks%20unspecified%20damages%20and%20aims%20to%20force%20DoorDash%20to%20change%20its%20business%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUber's%20case%20has%20no%20merit%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20DoorDash%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BTheir%20claims%20are%20unfounded%20and%20based%20on%20their%20inability%20to%20offer%20merchants%2C%20consumers%2C%20or%20couriers%20a%20quality%20alternative.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20November%2C%20data%20firm%20Earnest%20Analytics%20reports%20that%20DoorDash%20controls%2062.7%25%20of%20the%20delivery%20market%20nationally%2C%20followed%20by%20UberEats%2C%20which%20holds%2025%25%2C%20and%20Grubhub%20with%206.2%25.%20A%202024%20report%20of%20mystery%20shopper%20data%20from%20Intouch%20Insight%2C%20which%20collected%20experiences%20from%20300%20delivery%20orders%20from%20the%20three%20main%20delivery%20platforms%2C%20found%20DoorDash%20leads%20in%20customer%20satisfaction%2C%20with%20the%20app%20offering%20more%20promotions%2C%20delivering%20to%20the%20right%20location%2C%20and%20delivering%20the%20correct%20food%20more%20often%20than%20its%20other%20major%20competitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20found%20that%20DoorDash%20also%20dramatically%20outperformed%20its%20competitors%20in%20delivery%20time%2C%20with%20an%20average%20wait%20of%2026%20minutes%20and%2024%20seconds.%20Grubhub's%20average%20delivery%20time%20was%2035%20minutes%20and%2049%20seconds%2C%20while%20Uber%20Eats%20was%2038%20minutes%20and%204%20seconds%2C%20per%20Intouch%20Insight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20demand%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-diners-splurge-food-delivery-doordash-grubhub-ubereats-convenience-rules-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethird-party%20delivery%20services%3C%2Fa%3E%20remains%20high%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0DoorDash%20reported%20an%2018%25%20rise%20in%20orders%20year%20over%20year%20in%20its%20third%20quarter%20of%202024%2C%20with%20revenue%20growing%2025%25%20to%20%242.7%20billion%2C%20BI%20previously%20reported%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20criticism%20over%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-postmates-food-delivery-costs-twice-as-much-as-pickup-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efees%20charged%20by%20the%20apps%3C%2Fa%3E%20isn't%20new.%20Customers%20may%20be%20charged%20as%20much%20as%20twice%20the%20cost%20of%20their%20meal%20for%20ordering%20using%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frestaurants-owner-chef-moving-off-food-delivery-apps-doordash-ubereats-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edelivery%20app%3C%2Fa%3E%20compared%20to%20menu%20prices%2C%20and%20some%20restaurant%20owners%20find%20the%20apps'%20fees%20cut%20into%20their%20margins%20too%20much%20to%20be%20sustainable%2C%20BI%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20increasingly%20heard%20complaints%20from%20restaurants%20that%20DoorDash's%20tactics%20are%20limiting%20that%20freedom%20and%20punishing%20them%20for%20seeking%20better%20options%2C%26quot%3B%20Sarfraz%20Maredia%2C%20head%20of%20the%20Americas%20for%20delivery%20at%20Uber%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe%20hope%20this%20filing%20puts%20an%20end%20to%20those%20unfair%20practices%20so%20that%20restaurants%20can%20choose%20what's%20best%20for%20them%20without%20fear%20of%20penalty%20or%20retribution.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-doordash-anticompetitive-inflating-costs-unfair-business-practices-lawsuit-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739591912000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b0026c6630eb10385cc692%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-doordash-anticompetitive-inflating-cos